cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimizing the transmission rank in a multi-cell multi-user MISO broadcast channel, which involves information transmission and channel coding. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper considers a multi-cell environment with variable number of transmit beams at each base station, which involves network architecture and design. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper focuses on setting the transmission rank at each base station to satisfy Quality of Service (QoS) constraints, which involves system optimization and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with optimizing the transmission rank to increase the multiplexing gain and decrease interference, which are important factors in multimedia communication. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper presents an achievable region of transmission ranks that satisfy QoS constraints, which can be viewed as a game between the base stations and the users to maximize their respective utilities.
